<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://engineering.uic.edu/news-stories/che-department-does-its-part-to-fight-covid-19/">UIC ChE department does its part to fight COVID-19</a><br /></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Assistant Professor Sangil Kim and his </span><a style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;" href="https://polydream.wixsite.com/nanofluidics">Molecular Transports in Nanopores Lab</a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> are working to develop a vira, filtration mask that will provide strong protection along with high breathability and comfort. His group has been working on designing new nanoengineered membrane materials, some of which can be used for biomedical engineering, including different nanoporous filter materials for protective fabrics, respirators, and rapid separation of biological particles from clinical samples.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://blockclubchicago.org/2020/04/14/in-huge-endeavor-chicago-doctors-city-bring-thousands-of-coronavirus-tests-to-homeless-shelters/?fbclid=IwAR1J6OYGBmQw6ftbI09pEvcUcjaa3fkViMhiSmVbf_jYbWfaagCKXQP29os"><span style="font-weight: 400;">UIC Doctors Participate in &lsquo;Huge Endeavor&rsquo; to Bring Thousands Of Coronavirus Tests To Homeless Shelters</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">The news came Monday after Mayor Lori Lightfoot announced </span><a href="https://blockclubchicago.org/2020/04/13/homeless-shelters-will-now-get-visits-from-nurses-to-fight-coronavirus/?mc_cid=9dc764cb6d&amp;mc_eid=8a0c900cc0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">nurses will begin visiting every shelter across the city</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> to provide in-person education and screenings for the virus. The testing effort began last week when about 300 COVID-19 tests were administered to residents of </span><a href="https://www.pgm.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pacific Garden Mission</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Located at 1458 S. Canal St., the shelter is on the western side of the South Loop. Dr. Stockton Mayer of UIC&rsquo;s Division of Infectious Diseases co-led the testing effort alongside Dr. Elizabeth Davis from Rush Hospital.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://www.energy.gov/eere/amo/articles/energy-department-announces-notice-intent-issue-funding-high-performance-0"><span style="font-weight: 400;">DOE Announces a Notice of Intent to Issue Funding for High Performance </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Computing Consortium</span></a><br /><span style="font-weight: 400;">This unique</span> <a href="https://covid19-hpc-consortium.org/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">public-private consortium</span></a> <span style="font-weight: 400;">is one component of the High Performance Computing for Energy Innovation (HPC4EI) initiative. HPC4EI conducts two regular solicitations annually, one in the fall and one in the spring. The spring solicitation will target qualified industry partners to participate in short-term, collaborative projects with DOE National Laboratories that address key manufacturing challenges by applying modeling, simulation, and data analysis. The solicitation will encourage applicants to partner with universities and non-profit organizations located within federally designated Opportunity Zones and/or HBCUs. Selected projects will be awarded up to $300K to support computing cycles and work performed by DOE National Laboratories, universities, and non-profit partners.&nbsp;</span></p>
